4 SYNOPSIS:
5 Under existing law, the state shall not lend
6 money or its credit to any individual, association, or
7 corporation.
8 This bill would propose an amendment to the
9 Constitution of Alabama of 2022, to provide that the
10 Alabama Department of Economic and Community Affairs
11 may provide low-interest loans to qualifying chemical
12 and energy production facilities operating in the State
13 of Alabama as part of the State Energy Supply and
14 Chemical Trade Stabilization Act.
15
16
17 A BILL
18 TO BE ENTITLED
19 AN ACT
20
21 Proposing an amendment to the Constitution of Alabama
22 of 2022, to authorize the Alabama Department of Economic and
23 Community Affairs to provide low-interest loans under certain
24 circumstances.
25 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF ALABAMA:
26 Section 1. The following amendment to the Constitution
27 of Alabama of 2022, is proposed:
28 PROPOSED AMENDMENT
Page 1

PROPOSED AMENDMENT
HB555 INTRODUCED
29 (a) Notwithstanding any provisions of the Constitution
30 of Alabama of 2022 to the contrary, The Alabama Department of
31 Economic and Community Affairs is authorized to provide
32 low-interest loans to qualifying chemical and energy
33 production facilities in the State of Alabama as part of the
34 State Energy Supply and Chemical Trade Stabilization Act.
35 (b) Upon ratification of this constitutional amendment,
36 the Code Commissioner shall number and place this amendment as
37 appropriate in the constitution omitting this instructional
38 paragraph and may make the following nonsubstantive revisions:
39 change capitalization, hierarchy, spelling, and punctuation
40 for purposes of style and uniformity; correct manifest
41 grammatical, clerical, and typographical errors; revise
42 internal or external citations and cross-references; harmonize
43 language; and translate effective dates.
44 END OF PROPOSED AMENDMENT
45 Section 2. An election upon the proposed amendment
46 shall be held in accordance with Sections 284 and 285 of the
47 Constitution of Alabama of 2022, and the election laws of this
48 state. The appropriate election official shall assign a ballot
49 number for the proposed constitutional amendment on the
50 election ballot and shall set forth the following description
51 of the substance or subject matter of the proposed
52 constitutional amendment:
53 "Proposing an amendment to the Constitution of Alabama
54 of 2022, to authorize the Alabama Department of Economic and
55 Community Affairs to provide low-interest loans to qualifying
56 chemical and energy production facilities in the State of
